/*
:name: mod_untyped_io
:type: error
:error: has no declared type
:help: annotate the actual
*/

// Task 1p — an untyped `mod` input is no longer a definition-time error: it is
// a deferred template, specialized per call site on the actual's DECLARED type
// (decision 4). What IS an error is feeding an UNTYPED actual (here the bare
// literal `3`) into that boundary — a hardware port needs an explicit width.
mod f(a) -> (x:u8@[0]) { x = a }

mod top() -> (z:u8@[0]) {
  z = f(3)
}
